item.title: #530 (Another one)
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

[quote=“Pwnd, post:14, topic:261262”][quote author=Moparisthebest link=topic=345018.msg2661590#msg2661590 date=1234227443]

Ah, alright. So that just lets you use signed, but this isn’t a must, amirite?

Thanks.

Nope, using unsigned is much safer because they can’t pull that kind of stuff.
[/quote]But signed would probably decrease memory usage?

Or do they store the cache in… places you wouldn’t want it to be kept… [/quote]

It wouldn’t increase memory usage, just load times as a result of when bits of the cache is loaded into memory, they are requested from the server instead of from your hard disk. The advantages are many however, because they can’t access your hard drive or local network at all, making it impossible to detect you cheating based on checking files, running processes or anything of the like, it basically runs in a sandbox and can only contact the server it originated from.

If you run it signed, the load times and network usage would be reduced, but you would need to transparently redirect File accesses so that each client used it’s own cache (possibly by putting one of your own classes in place of sun’s File, FileInputStream etc), also you have to worry about all the other things they could possibly do to detect your cheating or running more than one instance of the client.

item.title: #530 (Another one)
item.dc:creator: @qauters qauters
item.description:
@qauters wrote:

[quote=“nueb35, post:15, topic:261262”][quote author=Moparisthebest link=topic=345018.msg2661590#msg2661590 date=1234227443]

Ah, alright. So that just lets you use signed, but this isn’t a must, amirite?

Thanks.

Nope, using unsigned is much safer because they can’t pull that kind of stuff.
[/quote]

speaking of unsigned, how exactly does that work? like how would you make an applet unsigned? just not call “providesignlink”?[/quote]
Running it unsigned is just running the client as an applet (init --> start etc).

Unsigned loads everything from the server into memory. It doesn’t increase memory though, because what is loaded on the signed client is the same as the unsigned client. What normally is loaded from the cache is now loaded from the server (making it slower obviously).

BAsh:
If I understand you correctly then the answer is no. Unsigned loads from the server and does not cache anything on your PC. It can’t, because it doesn’t have write permission ;).

Read full topic
